-- Turkey's Bank Asya shares jump after deputy PM says Ziraat interested
-- By Ece Toksabay
-- Wed Aug 06, 2014 07:24AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Aug 6 (Reuters) - Shares in Turkey's Islamic lender Bank Asya <ASYAB.IS> jumped 5.8 percent on Wednesday after Turkish Deputy Prime Minister Ali Babacan said state-run Ziraat Bank could buy Bank Asya.

